## interrupt-parent

**Value type:** `<phandle>`

Because the hierarchy of the nodes in the interrupt tree might not match the devicetree, the *interrupt-parent* property is available to make the definition of an interrupt parent explicit. The value is the phandle to the interrupt parent node (the interrupt controller). If this property is missing from a device, its interrupt parent is assumed to be its devicetree parent.

When set on a bus or container node (e.g. the root `/` node), it is inherited by all children that do not override it.

```dts
/* arch/arm64/boot/dts/allwinner/sun50i-h6.dtsi */
/ {
    interrupt-parent = <&gic>;
};
```
